[Normal Mode]

-- when cursor is on a string that is a bash command "shift + k" will open that commands man page for more information

-- pressing "." will repeat whatever edits you have just done in insert mode ("crtl + a" will do the same thing in insert mode).

[Insert Mode]

-- crtl+p to complete a string
++ (for more completions, see: https://georgebrock.github.io/talks/vim-completion/)

